JoAnne Gunderson Carner ( born April 4 , 1939 ) is an American former professional golfer .
Her 43 victories on the LPGA Tour led to her induction in the World Golf Hall of Fame .
She is the only woman to have won the U.S. 
Tiger Woods is the only man to have won the equivalent three USGA titles .
Arnold Palmer , Jack Nicklaus , and Carol Semple Thompson have also won three different USGA titles .
In 1981 , Carner was voted the Bob Jones Award , the highest honor given by the United States Golf Association in recognition of distinguished sportsmanship in golf .
She captained the 1994 U.S. Solheim Cup team .
